-- Ukraine’s Sovereign Debt Rose 0.4% in January, Ministry Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-03-15T17:59:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/ukraine-s-sovereign-debt-rose-0-4-in-january-ministry-says.html
Ukraine’s debt, including state
guarantees, increased 0.4 percent in January, the  Finance
Ministry  said.  Debt grew to $59.48 billion as of Jan. 31 from $59.22
billion a month earlier, the ministry said today in a  statement 
on its website.  Domestic debt rose to $20.26 billion from $20.21 billion at
the end of December, according to the ministry, based in the
capital, Kiev. Obligations to foreign creditors climbed to
$24.62 billion from $24.51 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
